title: Central Catholic's Alvin Pacheco is lehighvalleylive Football Player of the Week
text:
Alvin Pacheco , Central Catholic Alvin Pacheco (lehighvalleylive.com file photo) 
What did the senior do for the Vikings Saturday against Nazareth ? It might be easier to list what he didn't do, but we'll take a shot. 
Pacheco, a wide receiver/running back hybrid, was a workhorse as he took 19 carries for 249 yards and four touchdowns -- of 60, 43, 27 and 21 yards -- while adding three receptions for 79 yards. He also recorded an interception on defense and threw a key block in teammate Darnell Ferrell's 69-yard touchdown run. 
On the year, Pacheco has eight total touchdowns with 536 rushing yards and 146 receiving yards.
